(1270, 'Anonymous', 'Trump               Nation: A review of the beginning of the end', 'TrumpNation: The Art of Being the Donald', 'Everyone knows that when Donald was first             getting his feet wet in the real-estate development business his             incredibly wealthy ($300 millionaire) father gave him a $1 million             jump start loan. This amazing author, Tim O\'Brien, goes into detail             about that initial loan, but also the following $10 million, then             $30 million loans he received from his father\'s estate in his early             years.<br>             <br>             For me, the take away of this microscopic look into the life of one             of the dumbest human beings alive, was that some people just get             lucky and fail upwards. Almost comically, Donald has failed at most             of what he has done. He would have made many times more money than             he did over his lifetime had he just taken his father\'s initial loan             and put it in any stock market index fund.&nbsp; At every failure,             his father was able to bail him out. My FAVORITE example was when             his Dad, Fred Trump, wanted to give his boy Donny $2 million tax             free and fast for his failing casino. Instead of filing paper work             and paying taxes on such a large gift to his son, Fred Trump went to             Donny\'s casino and bought $2 million worth of poker chips, then             essentially just threw them away (never chased them), netting Donny             a cool $2 mill, tax free.<br>             <br>             Donald Trump is an idiot, at least by the close account of this             book. He is really not much more than son of a rich guy, rich idiot             who has never been allowed to fail completely and (at least before             the election that made us all question our sanity) has had only one             positive quality, that of being amazingly great to watch on reality             TV. O\'Brien spent A LOT of time with Trump by the sounds of it and             over all Trump comes off a a great guy. Nice to the people around             him, personable and good at not mixing business and the rest of             life. But good God, what a sad misguided idiot he seems to be too.<br>             <br>             If you want a great look into what it is to be Trump, this is the             best account I\'ve yet seen. God help us all, #ReadyForWarren2020', 'Timothy L. O\'Brien', 'Peter Ganim', 'History & Politics', 2016, '3 hÂ 25 m', 'Hachette Audio', '4', '3', '3.5', 'https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/51Hv8DBk13L._SX342_.jpg', 'https://www.amazon.com/TrumpNation-Art-Being-Donald/dp/B01GU48920/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1536666224&sr=1-1&keywords=TrumpNation+Timothy+OBrien', '12.78', 'https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1479850.TrumpNation', 'https://mega.nz/#F!yvoQTKCL!cHzM6YY3JU3b65OzxecnmA!Kq4gnYKA', '', '', 1, 0, 'Trump', '16'),
